        {
            "name": "Shadow",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Shadow Locations",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Shadows might lurk in any dimly lit area\u2014a corner in a crumbling ruin, a room lit by flickering candles, or a shaded forest at dusk. They travel to and from the Shadow Plane, though it is unclear if they do so via their own magic or by aligning themselves with a more powerful being capable of such planar shifting.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary pg. 289",
                                "alt": "Bestiary pg. 289",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                            },
                            "page": 289
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Locations",
                        "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "The mysterious undead known as shadows lurk in dark places and feed on those who stray too far from the light. Those who parley with shadows, typically by keeping them at bay with a glowing weapon, may learn great secrets, for they are ideal spies.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
